Column Comment.0: ANALYSIS IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for a sample analysis. Various types ofanalysis may be conducted on a sample. Samples may be derived from lithologiccuttings, fluid collection etc.
Column Comment.1: SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as thesource of information for this row.
Column Comment.2: VISCOSITY OBSERVATION NUMBER: A unique observation number for theviscosity analysis.
Column Comment.3: ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y or N flag indicating whether this row of data is currentlyeither active/valid (Y) or inactive/invalid (N).
Column Comment.4: EFFECTIVE DATE: The date that the data in this row first came into effect.
Column Comment.5: EXPIRY DATE: The date that the data in this row was no longer active or in effect.
Column Comment.6: OIL TEMPERATURE: Value for the oil temperature at the time of the viscositymeasurement
Column Comment.7: OIL TEMPERATURE OUOM: Temperature original unit of measure.
Column Comment.8: OIL TYPE: The type of oil being analyzed. For example, asphalt, crude, paraffin.
Column Comment.9: OIL VISCOSITY: Value for the viscosity, internal resistance to flow or friction of the oilin the sample.
Column Comment.10: OIL VISCOSITY OUOM: Oil viscosity original unit of measure.
Column Comment.11: OIL VISCOSITY UOM: The oil viscosity unit of measure. Multiple storage unitsmaybe required.
Column Comment.12: POUR POINT TEMPERATURE: Value for the lowest temperature at which a certainoil will flow. Pour point is an indication of the oil wax content.
Column Comment.13: POUR POINT TEMPERATURE OUOM: Pour point original unit of measure.
Column Comment.14: ROW_MANAGEMENT_GUID: This value may be used to provide a global uniqueidentifier for this row of data. Use of this column is not mandatory, but if used,optional PPDM NOT NULL and UNIQUE INDEX constraints provided in the datamodel DDL should be created.
Column Comment.15: PREFERRED INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating whether or not the oil viscosityanalysis is preferred.
Column Comment.16: REMARK: Narrative remarks about this row of data.
Column Comment.17: SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as thesource of information for this row.
Column Comment.18: STEP SEQUENCE NUMBER: A unique number indicating the sequence of the stepamong other steps in the preparation and processing of the sample. This column is asufficient method to keep track of what is done in the sample analysis. However, ifthe requirement for more complicated tracking such as two steps occurringsimultaneously or if steps are needed to be added to the initial procedure, use thetwo columns STEP_SEQ_NO1 and STEP_SEQ_NO2 in the tableANL_STEP_XREF.
Column Comment.19: VISCOSITY PRESSURE: The pressure at which the oil viscosity was measured.
Column Comment.21: VISCOSITY TEMPERATURE: The temperature at which the oil viscosity wasmeasured.
Column Comment.23: VISCOSITY VALUE: The value of the viscosity of the oil.
Column Comment.26: ROW CHANGED BY: Application login id of the user who last changed the row.
Column Comment.27: ROW CHANGED DATE: System date of the last time the row was changed.
Column Comment.28: ROW CREATED BY: System user who created this row of data.
Column Comment.29: ROW CREATED DATE: Date that the row was created on.
Column Comment.30: ROW_EFFECTIVE_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of datais effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data wasmade available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.31: ROW_EXPIRY_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data isno longer effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row ofdata was no longer available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.32: PPDM ROW QUALITY: A set of values indicating the quality of data in this row,usually with reference to the method or procedures used to load the data, althoughother types of quality reference are permitted.
